      <t>&lt;p&gt;The Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol for IPv6 (DHCPv6) provides a framework for passing configuration information to nodes on a network.  This document describes new options for DHCPv6 that SHOULD be used for booting a node from the network. [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
